Whatever you have accumulated into your life is a reflection of the person you have become

  • The biggest room in the world is the room for improvement
  • Most people want the interest before they make the investment
  • The secret for the success in life is for a man to be ready for the opportunity when it comes. If a person has not prepared himself sufficiently when the opportunity comes its too late
  • If you invest your time now, the future dividends would pay multiple rewards
  • If a person spends one hour a day every on the same subject for five years then that person will be an expert on that subject
  • If procrastination, laziness, overindulgence or bad temper is limiting your effectiveness then work hard to replace those bad habits with good ones.
  • Improving yourself requires self discipline, its is not always easy. There will be times when achievement requires you to do things that you donâ€™t like to do. Discipline however will help you stay on track
  • You must make deliberate efforts to grow and change in specific alignment with your goals
  • The mind likes what is the same but it learns from what is different
  • It is far more effective to make the internal changes first if you want the external things to change
  • Like a muscle when knowledge skills and habits go unused they dissipate
  • When people continually work on themselves they become sharper in their thinking
  • Self improvement leads not only to achievment but also a greater sense of fullfillment and satisfaction
